<A HREF="#A2228079Z20-F_HTM_BG76001A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	19. Financial risk management
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Management Board is responsible for implementing the finance policy and for ongoing financial risk management. Therefore the
	Management Board has established a Risk Management Committee, which is responsible for developing and monitoring of the Group's risk management policies especially regarding financial risks. Generally
	the committee provides an overview of financial risks on a quarterly basis to the Management Board as part of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	quarterly management
	reporting procedures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	principal financial instruments are comprised of short-term bank deposits at commercial institutions, bond funds, a note
	receivable, lease obligations and long-term debt. The main purpose of the financial asset instruments is to provide a return on investments with minimal risk. The main purpose of the financial
	liability instruments is to help fund the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	operations. The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	has various other financial
	assets and liabilities including trade receivables and trade payables, which arise directly from its operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	main risks arising from the Group's financial instruments are foreign exchange risk and credit risk. The measures taken by Management to manage each of these risks are summarized
	below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Transactions
	related to activities in the area of financial instruments require the prior approval of the Chief Financial Officer. The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	did not enter into any derivative financial instruments for hedging
	purposes in 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Management
	receives a weekly reporting of the current liquidity of the Group by entity. Furthermore, a monthly cash flow plan meeting has been established, where Management reviews the
	cash forecasts and the future development of flows of funds on an ongoing basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Foreign exchange risk
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	is exposed to foreign exchange risk to the extent that there is a mismatch
	between the currencies in which sales, purchases and borrowings are denominated and the respective functional currencies of subsidiaries of the Group. The functional currencies of the parent company
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet AG
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	and its subsidiaries are Euro, US Dollars and British Pound Sterling. The majority of the sale, purchase and borrowing transactions are
	denominated in the functional currency of the parent company or its subsidiaries. The primarily driver of foreign exchange risk derives from the intercompany loans made to subsidiaries and the note
	receivable each as summarized below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	has provided intercompany loans to its subsidiaries to finance their operations. The loans were granted in the local currency of
	the subsidiaries. Gains and losses from movements in exchange rates are recorded within other operating income or expense in the consolidated statement of comprehensive loss. As of December&nbsp;31,
	2015 the amount borrowed to
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet UK
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	totaled GBP&nbsp;6.6&nbsp;million (&euro;9.0&nbsp;million). A relative increase in the value of
	the Euro against British Pound Sterling of 10% would lead to a loss of &euro;0.8&nbsp;million. The amount of loans granted to
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
	America
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	totaled to USD&nbsp;4.5&nbsp;million (&euro;&nbsp;4.1&nbsp;million) as of December&nbsp;31, 2015. A relative increase in the value of the
	Euro against US Dollars of 10% would lead to a loss of &euro;0.4&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	financial assets include one note receivable denominated in British Pound Sterling in the amount of GBP 0.8&nbsp;million
	(&euro;&nbsp;1.1&nbsp;million). A relative increase in the value of the Euro against British Pound Sterling of 10% would lead to a loss of &euro;0.1&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-35
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>

<A NAME="A2228079Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FS76001_1_36">

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228079Z20-F_HTM_BG76001A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	19. Financial risk management (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For
	the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	generated 44.85% of its revenues in the eurozone. Additionally, the majority of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	sourcing
	transactions are also transacted in Euros in that zone.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	invoiced 75% in 2015, 90% in 2014 and 100% in 2013 of total revenues in Euro. As revenues in foreign currency usually
	correspond to costs which are incurred in the same currency, we consider the risk as minor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	significant exchange rates which have been applied during the years presented are disclosed in Note&nbsp;3.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Interest rate risk
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	principal interest-bearing positions are liabilities for bank borrowings and
	finance lease obligations. These liabilities are entirely at a fixed interest rate. As such, changes in market interest rates have no effect on future interest expenses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Credit risk
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Credit risk is the risk of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	suffering a financial loss as the result of its
	counterparties being unable to perform their obligations. The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	is exposed to credit risk from its operating activities (mainly trade receivables
	and customer loans) and from its financing activities, including deposits and investments with financial institutions. Therefore, the carrying amount of cash and cash equivalents, financial assets,
	and trade receivables represents the maximum credit exposure of &euro;37.4&nbsp;million (2014: &euro;&nbsp;52.6&nbsp;million).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	The Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	exposure to credit risk is influenced by the individual characteristics of each customer. However, Management also considers
	factors that influence the credit risk of its customer base, including the default risk of the industry and the country in which the customer operates.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	seeks to minimize such risk by entering
	into transactions with counterparties that are believed to be creditworthy business partners or with
	financial institutions which meet high credit rating requirements. In addition, the portfolio of receivables and customer advances is monitored on a continuous basis. Credit risk is limited to a
	specified amount with regard to individual receivables. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 there was only one customer loan, with only the current year interest payment unpaid and outstanding. The
	interest was fully settled in January 2016. As of December&nbsp;31, 2014 there were three customer loans of &euro;1.1&nbsp;million in total. For an overview of the aging of receivables
	and the allowance for doubtful accounts refer to note&nbsp;7.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Group limits its exposure to credit risk by investing only in bond funds and note receivables which are fully guaranteed by the financial institutions and therefore represents short
	term credit rating of A-3 based on Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor's or P-2 based on Moody's.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	bank deposit are held with financial institutions, which are rated BBB to A2 based on Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor's and Moody's.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Liquidity risk
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Liquidity risk is the risk that
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	might not have sufficient cash to meet its
	payment obligations associated with its financial liabilities that are settled by delivering cash or another financial asset.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	The Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	approach to
	managing liquidity is to ensure, as far as possible, that it will have sufficient
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-36
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>

	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	19. Financial risk management (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	liquidity
	to meet its liabilities when they are due, under both normal and stressed conditions, without incurring unacceptable losses or risking damage to the reputation of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	. Liquidity risk is
	countered by systematic, day-by-day liquidity management whose fundamental requirement is that solvency must be guaranteed at
	all times. A major responsibility of management is to monitor the cash balances and to set up and update cash planning on a monthly basis to ensure liquidity. At all times cash and cash equivalents
	are projected on the basis of a regular financial and liquidity planning. The monitoring includes the expected cash inflows on trade and other receivables together with expected cash outflows from
	trade and other payables.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	following are the remaining contractual maturities of financial liabilities and trade payables at the reporting date. The amounts are gross and undiscounted and include contractual
	interest payments.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	's short- and mid-term liquidity needs are currently covered. Due to the proceeds from the initial public offering as well as
	the follow-on offering, the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	considers the mid-term liquidity risk as minor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	20. Capital management
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Management's aim is to maintain a strong capital base so as to maintain investor, creditor and market confidence and to sustain future development of the business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-37
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	20. Capital management (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity
	is monitored by the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	using financial ratios. The equity used as a basis for determining the equity ratio corresponds to the
	equity disclosed in the Consolidated Statement of Financial Position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Part
	of the capital management strategy is to reduce the number of sale and leaseback transactions for 3D printing equipment used in the production of printed products for customers. As
	a result of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	increased liquidity from its public equity offerings, certain lease contracts will be terminated prior to their scheduled
	maturity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet's
</I>
</FONT>

	capital structure as of the end of the reporting periods 2015 and 2014 was as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating
	lease expenses were kEUR 813, kEUR 348, and kEUR 377 in the financial years 2015, 2014, and 2013, respectively. Operating lease expenses are primarily related to the rental
	agreements for real estate regarding our foreign operations and a new rented building at our German headquarters put in service in 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Lessor
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	leased five of its self-produced 3D printers to customers. Under the lease
	contracts,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	bears a majority of the substantial risks and rewards of the underlying assets.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	operating lease income was kEUR 225, kEUR 169 and kEUR 126 in the financial years 2015, 2014, and 2013, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	22. Commitments, contingent assets and liabilities
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with the enforcement of
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	intellectual property rights, the acquisition of third-party intellectual property
	rights, or disputes related to the validity or alleged infringement of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	's or a third-party's intellectual property rights, including patent
	rights,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	has been and may in the future be subject or party to claims, negotiations or complex, protracted litigation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	December&nbsp;1, 2015, the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	signed a definitive agreement to form an equity joint venture with Suzhou Meimai Fast
	Manufacturing Technology&nbsp;Co.,&nbsp;Ltd. ("Meimai") to pursue opportunities in the industrial 3D printing market in China.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet AG
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	is
	committed to make a capital contribution of RMB 19.2&nbsp;million (&euro;2.7&nbsp;million) as part of its joint venture arrangement with Meimai.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
	AG's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	capital contribution will be made in three tranches of RMB 6.5&nbsp;million (&euro;0.9&nbsp;million) in each of 2016, 2017 and 2018.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	23. Related party transactions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Related party transactions at
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	mainly consist of transactions with individuals on the Management Board and Supervisory Board.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Key
	management is defined as those individuals having authority and responsibility for planning, directing and controlling the activities of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	within their function and within the interest of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	.
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	23. Related party transactions (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Management
	Board remuneration currently consists of a fixed monetary remuneration, other fixed benefits (including
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	car allowances
	and contributions to a direct contribution plan), and a variable bonus.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At
	December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014, amounts of kEUR 0 and kEUR 276 were accrued for Management Board compensation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	's Chief Executive Officer agreed to personally guarantee EUR 75,000 of a loan from Bayerische Hypo- und Vereinsbank AG, Munich,
	Germany, to the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	. Three of the shareholders of
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	pursuant to an agreement, dated
	September&nbsp;1, 2010, each agreed to reimburse the Chief Executive Officer EUR 18,750 in case
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	defaults on the loan and the Chief Executive
	Officer was required to pay any sums under his personal guarantee. The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	paid an interest rate of 6.00% per annum on the guaranteed amount to each
	guarantor. The guarantee and the agreement with the shareholders were terminated in March 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Transactions with related parties
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A related party relationship could have an effect on the profit and loss and financial position of the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	. Defined as related parties
	are individuals or other third parties with whom
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	has common
	control relationships.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	main transactions with other related individuals were the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Franz
	Industriebeteiligungen AG, Augsburg, Germany, is owned by Mr.&nbsp;Rudolf Franz who worked as an external consultant at
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	until June&nbsp;30, 2013. Since July, 1, 2013, he has been the Chief Financial Officer of
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet AG
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	. For his external consulting services, Franz
	Industriebeteiligungen AG, received compensation on a regular basis which was split into a fixed and variable component, amounted to the following: kEUR 99 (kEUR 70 fixed and kEUR 29 variable) for
	2013. Other transactions with Franz Industriebeteiligungen AG comprise the rental of office space in Augsburg, Germany. Rental expenses amounted to kEUR 2, in each of 2015, 2014 and 2013. In addition,
	Franz Industriebeteiligungen AG received payments related to the use of certain paintings which are placed in the administrative building in Friedberg. Associated rental expenses amount to kEUR 2 in
	each of 2015, 2014, and 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Further,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	acquired goods amounting to kEUR 38, kEUR 29, and kEUR 20 in 2015, 2014 and 2013 from 'Schlosserei und Metallbau
	Ederer', which is owned by the brother of Dr.&nbsp;Ingo Ederer, the Chief Executive Officer of
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	24. Equity
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On October&nbsp;23, 2013, the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	completed its initial public offering of 7,475,000 American Depositary Shares ("ADSs") at a public
	offering price of USD&nbsp;13.00 per ADS. Of the 7,475,000 ADSs sold in the public offering, 5,600,000 were sold by the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	and 1,875,000 were
	sold by its
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-41
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=7,SEQ=140,EFW="2228079",CP="VOXELJET AG",DN="1",CHK=926064,FOLIO='F-41',FILE='DISK129:[16ZAV1.16ZAV76001]FS76001A.;16',USER='JTAM',CD='31-MAR-2016;16:23' -->
<A NAME="A2228079Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FS76001_1_42">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228079Z20-F_HTM_BG76001A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	24. Equity (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	shareholders
	(the "Selling Shareholders"). As a result of the offering, the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	received net proceeds of approximately
	USD&nbsp;64.5&nbsp;million, or approximately &euro;46.8&nbsp;million, after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions and &euro;2.2&nbsp;million in offering costs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	April&nbsp;16, 2014, the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	completed a follow-on offering of 3,000,000 ADSs at a public offering price of USD&nbsp;15.00 per
	ADS. Net proceeds from the follow-on offering to the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	were approximately USD&nbsp;41.4&nbsp;million. On April&nbsp;24, 2014, the
	underwriters in the follow-on offering purchased 450,000 ADSs from the Selling Shareholders pursuant to the overallotment option they were granted in the follow-on offering. The net proceeds to the
	Selling Shareholders were approximately USD&nbsp;6.4&nbsp;million, or approximately &euro;4.6&nbsp;million. The
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	did not receive
	any proceeds from the sale of ADSs by the Selling Shareholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At
	December&nbsp;31, 2015, 3,720,000 no-par value ordinary shares were issued and outstanding. There is only a single class of ordinary shares with the same rights, preferences and
	restrictions. Each share entitles the holder to one vote at the shareholders' meeting. Shareholders participate in the profits according to their share in the share capital, based on their number of
	shares held. The general shareholders' meeting resolves the appropriation of the balance sheet profit established in the annual financial statements and the dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Articles of Association authorize the Management Board, subject to the consent of the Supervisory Board, to increase the
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Company's
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	registered share capital in one or more tranches by up to kEUR 1,860 new no par value ordinary shares against contribution in cash or in kind until May&nbsp;26, 2019.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	25. Subsequent Events
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In February 2016,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	concluded three loan agreements with Kreissparkasse Augsburg, Germany, in an aggregate amount of
	&euro;4.0&nbsp;million to finance the construction of new office and production facilities in Friedberg comprised of (i)&nbsp;a loan agreement in the amount of
	&euro;2.0&nbsp;million with a fixed interest rate of 2.47% per annum due December&nbsp;30, 2025, (ii)&nbsp;a loan agreement in the amount of &euro;1.0&nbsp;million with a
	fixed interest rate of 2.72% per annum due December&nbsp;30, 2030 and (iii)&nbsp;a loan agreement in the amount of &euro;1.0&nbsp;million with a variable interest rate of 1.75% per
	annum, which can be terminated by either party upon three months' notice. Among other terms, the loan agreements contain (i)&nbsp;certain covenants, including that
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	deposit
	&euro;2.0&nbsp;million with Kreissparkasse Augsburg until it has reached certain ratio with respect to its ability to
	service the debt by the end of 2019, and (ii)&nbsp;change of control provisions concerning the ownership of the Company by its executive officers, Dr.&nbsp;Ingo Ederer and Rudolf Franz. In case
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	fails to meet that ratio by the end of its business year 2019,
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	is obliged to pledge
	&euro;2.0&nbsp;million for the benefit of the lender. In addition, the land owned by
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	voxeljet
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	upon which the facilities will be built will
	serve as collateral under the loan agreements. Management expects that construction will commence in May 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-42
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

</UL>
<FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<A HREF="#A2228079ZEX-8_1_HTM_TOC_KA76001_2">
	Subsidiaries of voxeljet AG
</A>

<BR>
<!-- SEQ=,FILE='QUICKLINK',USER=JTAM,SEQ=,EFW="2228079",CP="VOXELJET AG",DN="2" -->

</EFX_EXHIBIT_8>

<DIV CLASS="eolNewPage"></DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage3"></A>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM"></A>
<EFX_EXHIBIT_12>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_12"></A>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>
<A HREF="#A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM_16ZAV76001_3">
	QuickLinks
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=3>
	-- Click here to rapidly navigate through this document
</FONT>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_BASECOLOR,"BLACK" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_DEFAULTFONT,"FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TABLESHADECOLOR,"#CCEEFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_STABLERULES,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_DTABLERULES,"BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE #000000 2.25PT;" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_SCRTABLERULES,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;" -->
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_DCRTABLERULES,"BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE #000000 2.25PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;" -->
</FONT>
</P>
<!-- TOC_END -->
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM_KC76001_EXHIBIT_12_1">
</A>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM_TOC_KC76001_1">
</A>
<BR>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Exhibit&nbsp;12.1
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM_KC76001_CERTIFICATION_OF_CHIEF_EXECUTI__CER03515">
</A>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_1_HTM_TOC_KC76001_2">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	CERTIFICATION OF CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER
<BR>
	PURSUANT TO SECTION&nbsp;302 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF&nbsp;2002
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	I,
	Dr.&nbsp;Ingo Ederer, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	1.
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	I
	have reviewed this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;20-F of voxeljet AG;
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	2.
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Based
	on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements
	made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	3.
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Based
	on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the
	financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	4.
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	registrant's other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange
	Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and
	have:
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(a)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Designed
	such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that
	material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is
	being prepared;
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(b)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Designed
	such internal control over financial reporting, or cause such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to
	provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting
	principles;
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(c)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Evaluated
	the effectiveness of the registrant's disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of
	the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(d)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Disclosed
	in this report any change in the registrant's internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant's most recent fiscal
	quarter (the registrant's fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant's internal control over
	financial reporting.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	5.
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	registrant's other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the
	registrant's auditors and the audit committee of the registrant's board of directors (or other persons performing the equivalent functions):
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(a)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	All
	significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to
	adversely affect the registrant's ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(b)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Any
	fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant's internal control over
	financial reporting.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DD>
</DL>
<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;WIDTH:80%;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
</FONT>
</P>

<TR>
<!-- TABLE COLUMN WIDTHS SET -->

</TD>
<TD WIDTH="12PT" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="48%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
</TD>
<!-- TABLE COLUMN WIDTHS END -->
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="BOTTOM">
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	/s/&nbsp;DR.&nbsp;INGO EDERER
<BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" COLOR="#000000">
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Dr.&nbsp;Ingo Ederer
<BR>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<I>
	Chief Executive Officer
<BR>
	(Principal Executive Officer)
</I>
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_3_HTM_KG76001_CERTIFICATION_OF_CHIEF_EXECUTI__CER04880">
</A>
<A NAME="A2228079ZEX-12_3_HTM_TOC_KG76001_2">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	CERTIFICATION OF CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER
<BR>
	PURSUANT TO 18 U.S.C. SECTION&nbsp;1350,
<BR>
	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO SECTION&nbsp;906 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF&nbsp;2002
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with the Annual Report on Form&nbsp;20-F of voxeljet AG (the "Company") for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 as
	filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the "Report"), the undersigned, Dr.&nbsp;Ingo Ederer, Chief Executive Officer of the Company, hereby certifies, pursuant to 18
	U.S.C. Section&nbsp;1350, that:
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(1)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	Report fully complies with the requirements of Section&nbsp;13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended; and
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(2)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	information contained in the Report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations of the Company.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</UL>

</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	CERTIFICATION OF CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER
<BR>
	PURSUANT TO 18 U.S.C. SECTION&nbsp;1350,
<BR>
	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO SECTION&nbsp;906 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF&nbsp;2002
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with the Annual Report on Form&nbsp;20-F of voxeljet AG (the "Company") for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 as
	filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the "Report"), the undersigned, Rudolf Franz, Chief Financial Officer of the Company, hereby certifies, pursuant to 18 U.S.C.
	Section&nbsp;1350, that:
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(1)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	Report fully complies with the requirements of Section&nbsp;13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended; and
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(2)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	information contained in the Report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations of the Company.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</UL>
